SIRT method (Simultaneous Iterative Reconstruction Technique)

We set up system of linear equations with slowness in cells as unknowns and find an approximate solution using least squares method and bounds for maximal and minimal speed.

Not great yet (Mar 26, 2024).

text = dict(fontsize='xx-large', 
        horizontalalignment='center', verticalalignment='center')
   
def plot(s, **kwargs):
    """Plot the ray segment and the dot in the middle of the segment."""
    ax.plot(*np.array([s.start_coordinates, s.end_coordinates]).T, **kwargs)
    center = (s.end_coordinates + s.start_coordinates) / 2 
    ax.plot(*center,".")

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8,8))

for cell in t.grid.all_cells:
    ax.text(cell.x+0.5*cell.dx, cell.y+0.5*cell.dy, cell.id, color='gray', **text)

for s in t.allsegments:
    plot(s)    
    
for j in [0,3,13,15]:    
    cell = t.grid.all_cells[j]
    seg = [i for i in t.allsegments if cell == i._storage]

In[6]:
start = time.time()
A,b = t._matrices['A'], t._matrices['b']
x = np.full(A.shape[1], 1/speed_min)
sol = least_squares(lambda x:A@x-b, x, bounds=[1/speed_max, 1/speed_min], gtol=None)
sol = sol.x
print(f"Least squares finished in {1000*(time.time()-start):.0f} ms.")

for s,c in zip(sol,t.active_cells):
    seg = [i for i in t.allsegments if c == i._storage]
    c.velocity = 1/s
    for sg in seg:
        sg.speed = 1/s
    
t.plot(speed_min=speed_min, speed_max=speed_max, grid=False)    
plt.suptitle(f"Tomogram from scipy least squares, {len(t.grid.all_cells)} cells.")

Least squares finished in 4017 ms.

Text(0.5, 0.98, 'Tomogram from scipy least squares, 400 cells.')

SIRT for fine grid and with compensated reaction time

In SIRT method there is possible to handle reaction time, a time which is added to each time from one node to another.

In[7]:
t = tomo.Tomo (speeds=data_velocity, nx=nx, ny=nx, symmetric=True, eps=0.01)

t.fix_velocity_EBSI()
report = t.do_SIRT_method(fix_reaction_time=True, **speeds)
print(report)

ax = t.plot(grid=False, **speedsp)    
plt.suptitle(f"Tomogram with rays from numpy SIRT, {len(t.grid.all_cells)} cells.")

SIRT finished in 100 ms.
Speed interval: min=300.0 for 12 segments, max=1400.0  for 1031 segments
Reaction time is 0.7142857142857143 ms.
